<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I write this to help wizards for it is getting harder and harder for wizards out there to get groups. This is because, in my oppinion,they are trying to show off or to be the hero. Some want to see their name in lights, so to speak, X has been slain by (input wiz name). Wizards have a massive amount of power at their finger tips and with this power comes a big responsibility.<P>If you are soloing it IS about delivering the biggest ,fastest nuke you can produce to end the fight as quickly as possible. But if you are in a group it is about letting everyone do their job. Tanks take pride in their battle scars, so let them,healers enjoy takin care of their patients after or during a fight, so let them, and so on and so on. What I am about show you is ,in my oppion, the best way to salvage the rep of our class in the world of Norrath.<P>The Veil of Desception<P>I call it this because with this tactic you fool the mob into thinking you are of no threat to them. The tanks job is to wrestle with the mob, distracting them from the true threat which are the casters in the second rank. This is not to say tanks are worthless cause they are not. They are our best ally and you best have respect for them or you are dead LOADING PLEASE WAIT.......( <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/redface.gif">)><P>Below i will simulate a battle and show the tactics I use. This may not be the best and some may know better ways, but it works for me and gets me invited into groups. When I get into a group that might be comprised of 2 or 3 tanks, cleric,druid/shaman, and any other caster, I give a tell to anyone that can cast a stun spell. I ask them to load it and try to get them to play along in the fun game of chain stunning. This in my oppinion is one of the best spell strains in the game. It helps the healer types spend less mana healing, it keeps the mob centered on the tanks, who get  free swings, and keeps them at the top of the aggro list. If you have a rogue that is your puller you allow him/her the opportunity to run around for backstabs which falls into their strong suite.<P>That being said here is my tactic:<P>1: First spell I cast is stun, wizards stun spell does 50pts., and or markers 200pts, I use the lower one and have the other loaded just incase the first is ressisted, which can piss the mob off. Do not know the percentage chance of the mob aggroing on you for ressisted spells but it can happen so be prepared. With such little damage I am probably last on the aggro list. Some say clerics since most do not engage, but they will heal or have done so depending on the damage sustained by puller, druids/shaman have more than likely cast regen on everyone, so they have been recognized as a potential threat.<P>2:Second spell I cast is shock of fire 110pts damage. This is my 16th lvl spell, yes it is little damage but hey it is the begining of the fight. This may cause me to move form 6th to 5th on the aggro list. I repeat this as my 3rd and 4th spells cast waiting for my stun to recycle. All this time the other stunners have hopefully cast their stun spell/s.<P>3: My stun spell is my 5th cast. The fight has been going for awhile and the mob should be at half or maybe less and you are still at the bottom of the aggro list. ( <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/redface.gif">)><P>4: My 6th spell I unleash is my biggest nuke(Ice Comet) 1120pts. I can almost here the whipcrack of the mobs neck as he turns to look at me. I have totally dropped the Veil of Desception and it realizes how dangerous I truely am. As our eyes meet I give a sheepish grin and a wink as it trys to turn and run or it may even be falling to a knee as the spark of life fades from its eyes.<P>The tanks give a cheer marveling at their skill, the healers tend to their patients and I sit and meditate contemplating the marvels of the Universe. With a tougher mob I have successfully cast 7 to 10 shocks (770 to 1100), 3 stuns (150) and a big nuke (1120),without getting touched by the mob.<P>The Art of the Fox<P>I say this because during the course of grouping people may never notice that you have not asked for many buffs outside sow or maybe clarity(if possible),just to ease the day a little. It may be after your second grouping that they will notice you are unlike most Wizards out there, screaming for heals or buffs;and running around like a chicken with their head cut off trying to shake the mob,. Your cunning and craftiness has won you respect like the Fox. I take great pride when i get tells or even group says that go " Man Ark you do not get hit that much" and my response is "Hmm I really have not noticed that" (Wink Wink) ( <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/redface.gif">)><P>So for the wizards out there, we are not as diverse as the other casters and we do not have pets to defend us, only our intellect and tactics will help us. wether it is dueling,soloing, or even grouping be smart know your strenghts and weaknesses and play to both and you will actually be stronger.<P><BR>Arkanys Spellfyre<BR>52nd circle wizard<BR>Walker of the Way and Student of the Art.<BR>The Rathe server
</FONT>
