<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I have been using somewhat of this tactic for a while though I never really thought to go back to shock of fire  (I was using more spells in the 200 range).  Thanx for reminding me of what I so carelessly forgot.  <P>As for your tactic, I tried it out in a group in LGuk the other day and it rocked.  I was in a weird group where people were pulling without thought and the danger level continued to increase.  A sentinel was pulled along with 3 other mobs and I thought we would be evacing quite soon (we had no chanter) but the 2 necros kept some of the mobs Screamed and we ended up fine.  I stunned the sentinel as much as possible and hit it with Flame Shock about 7 times before unleashing Conflag.  After the sentinel dropped we were fine.  <P>Later, however, we got into another battle and our paladin was doing the best he could to give heals (yes we had no cleric either) along with the other paladin.  <P>I would begin to cast evac but then a lay hands would come in and i would have to duck only to stand up again and recast because someone else was dropping quickly.  Also, like every other wizard, my evac hotkey anounces i am casting evac and then does a /cast 4.  <P>Sadly, we lost a necro in the battle but at the time i cast an evac he told me to duck because he thought he could tap some life.  He did but it was not enough.<P>When my evac went off, our other necro had 1/8 of a bub left of health (bout 13 hp), and our paladins were down to about a bub each.  <P>I, on the other hand, evaced with full health.  To anyone who is fighting mobs at higher levels, I highly suggest using this tactic!!!  <P>Thanx for the info Ark!<P>Zyr
