<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I am level 38 and use similar tactics.  I'm sure my tactics will change a bit as i level, but this is my standard Strategy for now.  I sit on my butt as the puller brings in the mobs.  I target my puller and assist him.  I wait for the mob to get a little damaged.  I then stand up and hit it with 2-3 16th level fire spells (110 each).  Then i let it loose and hit it with my big ice spell for about 320pts.  By this time the mob is just standing there wishing it could run away thanks to the ranger or druid or me  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"> that snared it (If i'm the snarer i do this before i sit on my butt).  For the most part my group just goes on with life and things are nice.  Many times, either the same day or days later, I will get a tell from someone I grouped with.  They will say wow after you left it was a lot more work to take down the mobs.  We didn't know what we had till you were gone.  In my opinion if played right the wizard is the silent partner that nobody knows about, but everyone eventually misses.<P>Meleena Harpell -- 38th Wizard -- Erollisi Marr<P>"I'm a little fuzzy on this whole good bad thing"  -- Dr. Peter Venkman
