I too use a version of this strategy and do very well with it.<P>One time I was complimented was soon after I had joined an orc highway group.  The group needed an extra body after a bad pull had killed them off and one of them never came back to regroup.<P>The first comment after a few pulls was "Wow, we are pulling fast now!"  It wasn't directed specifically at me but I smiled at the comment.  <P>The compliment came after a very bad pull.  The ranger came in with, a priest and a warrior.  As she came in, 2 more warriors spawned nearby and aggro'd as well.  All of us killed the priest right away (of course).  But the cleric announce OOM soon after that as the tanks were taking quite a beating.  I nuked one of the warriors, backed up and parked it with a root once it aggro'd me.  Then I chained my biggest (at the time) nuke twice on the one they were fighting, killing it.  We were then able to kill the unrooted mob and then the rooted one without too much trouble.<P>Everyone was very appreciative of my contribution after it was over and none of them minded having to wait for me to med back after going OOM   <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/smile.gif"><P>Tielk<BR>
