Ah, the Veil of Deception.  I have to agree with most of this post, as well as a lot of the responses.  Most groups I am with don't realize how important I am unless they were holding a spawn without me and I joined, or I leave and they have to hold a spot after I leave.  <P>I wanted to add my thoughts to the thread, and ask a discussion.  I have read a lot about 'not using your biggest nuke'.  Now, I'm only 29th level, so my biggest nuke is Inferno Shock for 237, but it is also my most mana effecient nuke at 1.75 hp/mana.  <P>IMHO, the above strategy would work just as well with a stun, med, stun, med, ice comet, med, ice comet, but save a lot of mana.  I don't see how a bunch of small nukes at less mana effeciency has any benefit over a large nuke later in the battle, except to make everybody feel like you're contributing throughout the whole fight.  <P>Buhwheat WuppinPeNub<BR>Morrel-Thule
