Well I would like to point out two things commented on in previous posts. One was Sriel He pointed out that AoE spells are more mana efficent per DMG. which is unarguably true, however unless each mob is firmly bening attacked by a tank or you have rooted each mob. you will find some Mobs quickly agroing to you. I like the AoE line and I feel it does have a time and place. but typically in my experience only when you are adding to what the tanks are already doing. Second a note to Buhwheat The reason you want to lay off your big boom is it will stick you at the top of the argo list and you will have to heavily rely on your stuns/roots/enstills and the like.. I dont know about you but I rather not depend on those spells. (dont get me wrong I love em.. just not going to make them my saving grace)<P>Aelstyn Melarn<BR>Drinal<BR>Wizard of the 25th Circle of power
