<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I agree that I don't want to rely on root-n-nuke in most group situations, but I still want to make sure I understand the way the agro system works.  <P>Lets say that in the first 30 seconds of a battle my tank is going to build up 1200 pts of hate with the mob. <P>If during that time, I cast a 200 pt nuke every say 6 seconds, the mob shouldn't agro on me.  So I've cast 5 nukes at 200pts each.  <P>On the other hand, if I did nothing for the first 25 seconds, then cast ice commet, I have done 1k damage as well, but I have done it all at once, for a greater mana effeciency.  <P>Now, given that my total damage output was the same, as I understand it, the mob is no more likely to agro on me having cast one big nuke than 5 little nukes, the differences being that I have spent less mana (good) and I've sat on my butt more (good because I've medded more, bad because I'm bored.)<P>Enlighten me.<P>--Buhwheat
</FONT>
