<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Great post .. and oh, so true.<P>I am a 53 Wizard on Luclin server and these tactics are absolutely necessary at the post 50 game. For those burning wizards out there, when mobs are whacking on you for 100+ triple hits you are not going to last long even with mana skin, so aggroing mobs onto yourself in a group will only do 2 things.<P>1) You die - goodbye group evacer.<P>2) Goodbye evacer - group prolly dies.<P>Now - for all the benefits of this tactic, to train on how to most effectively use your nukes and stuns - find a nice outside area where snare can be used and group with a cleric and enchanter (all of you have stuns).<P>Learn, by working together, how to time your stuns so each is contributing as well as to get an idea of how often your stun line gets resisted.<P>With this information you can then talk to any enchanter/cleric in any group and work out a stun plan. I have heard clerics say they don't stun because they are always medding for heals - ironically, in a coordinated wizard-cleric-enchanter stun group the tanks need very little healing and the mana use is minimum. Can you say, "Hmmmm."<P>In a bigger picture - as you grow with your wizard, find other classes to group with in pairs or 3's. Talk about what you can do and listen to them about what they can do. Learn their skills. Try different things. I have grouped with every class to simply learn how to make the combos successful. Even tanks in the mid 40's to 50's.<P>If the tank hasn't been 'trained' they are a bit reluctant to take on mobs without a cleric at these levels .. but once they see you cast snare and ice comet and that they can just walk behind the mob coming after you (yes, aggroing a mob can be good) and beat it to death they will call you god. [When aggro goes back to tank, just get close to mob and cast a medium nuke -  poof, instant aggro again.]<P>Necro's are my favorite partners - same plan, except a necro dot will easily out aggro Ice Comet (very high taunt spells) .. and this is fine because then the necro becomes the focus of the mob while you sit and med and the pet plays warrior. When the mob gets to about half health, root, pull pet off and let the necro dot .. both of you can sit and med. By the time the mob is dead you have both 'used' only about 20 mana (more - but you have been medding) and are ready for the next pull. Add a chanter just for an extra dot and clarity and you can pull non stop.<P>I could go on with each class, including dual wizards, but the point is - work with all of them to learn what they can do with you and how to compliment each others abilities. Amazing how this knowledge will blend into any full group you get into as you can share your knowledge with the others. Tell them what you plan to do and teach them. The worst thing in EQ is being in an uncoordinated group, no matter how 'balanced' it should be.<P>Graffenlaff Delaffensa<BR>53 Wandering Wizard - Luclin
</FONT>
