Finally an intelligent thread on Wizard tactics... <P>One thing I'd like to add is on the subject of the AE nukes.. I've been told that in a multiple pull, the extra aggros are on the same aggro as the mob the warrior is meleeing with. <P>I rarely use ae spells because It's not a good complement to chanter mezzing. But I've tried them a few times out of curiosity and unless I overburned, The extra mobs never looked at me twice even if they hadn't been hit by the melee.<P>And GraffenLaf, I know what you mean about "training the melees" Telling them to stop taunting so the mob can run after you usually earns you an "are you nuts" look... Even if it is one of the best tactics I've found to be able to group with clericless melees. It's Extremely efficient too, I believe you can take out pretty much anything that way.<P>Oh, and I've had friends tell me after a raid I couldn't attend that they would have needed a wizard to really pull it off... that just gives me a warm fuzzy...
