<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Benevolents: You need to nuke less.  You're just getting to the lvl where the Wizard separates himself from the other classes, and we finally have the mana and the spells to out-dam/out-taunt the other classes (importantly - tanks).  It'll take you a while to learn how much you can nuke without being aggro'd on, but I'd take a guess at first nuke when mob gets to 75%, and give 10 to 20 seconds between nukes after that.  Push the limits a bit and aggro a few when it's safe.  Learn just how much they'll take before they come so when you over-pull you know just how much you can dump without getting killed.<P>As for pulling things onto myself, I do it all the time (on purpose, almost never by accident).  Spent most of yesterday hunting in OT in a group that wasn't all that great.  I was the highest lvl in there, and we were dropping whites and yellows pretty constantly (usually red to rest of group), but sometimes we'd pull one that was a pretty good red even to me.  I'd just make sure it was snared, chain-cast my biggest nuke twice, and go for a jog with the rest of the group beating on it.  Throw in a few more nukes on occasion to make sure it doesn't turn back on the rest of them, and we were able to take down anything we encountered.  Using this type of strategy, I'll take almost anyone as a partner when I'm soloing, opens up kiting as a strategy to pretty much every class in the game.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
