<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I couldn't agree with you more! My regular group consists of 3 palis, a cleric, a druid, and me (the wizzy). We have been doing the chain stun deal so long now that our cleric rarely heals even after a tough battle. We always lead with my stun - then the 3 palis, one after the other, then the cleric. I toss in a nuke somewhere in there and by the time by turn comes up, my stun has cycled and we start over again. I rarely get below 70m so I always have plenty for the emergency evac or burn downs.<P>Using this strategy, we have had nights in OT that we would pull as fast as the palis could get new mob - usually one would peel off near the end of the fight to get another - for over 3 hours! The only break we would take were bathroom/soda/smoke breaks. We manager to pull in over a bub an hour like this!<P>Wizzies may be broken, but if we play within the constraints set upon us and use our brains - like a good wizzy always does - we are a huge asset to any exp group.<P>I received the greatest compliment from a pick up group the other night. I had put together a group with a bunch of people that I had grouped with before, but they didn't know each other. After about 10 straight mobs the tank commented that he always loves to group with me because we rake in the exp. The rest of the group quickly chimed in and agreed - even going as far as saying they look for me when they log on in case I am near by and have an open spot for them!<P>Play smart and you will never have a problem finding groups, they will find you!
</FONT>
