Very nice post.<P>Sound tactics. I have used these tactics since I got my first stun spell.<P>The only problem is that unless you play with the same people each night your chances of picking up a group is already hurt to start with. Because of the POOR perception of people have of wizards.<P>Wizards are quite usefull and I loved playing mine.... but they are not as usefull as other classes and on EQ everyone only wants to build the Best Group they can and wizards are the last class accepted.<P>I realized this Fully when I started playing my twinks. I would be leading a group and a wizard would be LFG. I would ask my group if they wanted him and in unison I would hear NOO!!  Wizards suck!<P>This was very painfull to be on the inside of what was going on when I was LFG for hours with my wizard.<P>Anyway if you can group with friends on a regualr basis you can prove your skill as a wizard but once you get post 50, people do not and can not afford to have an infierior class in there group. And will opt to save that spot for some one who they feel they need like the standard make up of 3tanks one enchanter, one cleric and one other.. anything but wizard.<P>I dont mean to discourage you. but that is why I have retired my wizard at 51.<P>I hope you all have better luck than I did.
