<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
hey, i agree that in a nice big group, this is a really good way to go about things.  however, at lvl 22, im more used to smaller, less balanced groups, where i am the main damage dealer and the group heavily depends on me. i am currently hunting gnolls in SK (they all con red to me) and im usually in a group with a fake tank (ranger, rogue, etc.) and an enchanter or druid, and if i dont kill the mob, we're dead. now, it obviously makes it easier with a druid (sow and snare) since i can deal with agroed mods by kiting, however if thats not the case i have to make sure i deal out the most damage i can without dying. i do this by casting shock of fire (lvl 4 16dmg) right after the fighter makes his first hit. this is basically just a tester, since all the gnolls are red i have to be very careful about resisting. if it hits for full damage i immediately use fire shock (lvl 16 110dmg) and if its partially resisted i use lightning bolt (lvl 16 125dmg). i then do my agro test- i walk up to the mob and see if it will turn away from the tank to hit me... if it does i back up and test again in a couple secs; if it doesnt i nuke again with the same nuke. now, since it didnt hate me enuf before hand to hit me when i was point blank, 9 out of 10 times it will not leave the tank for me and if it does the tank gets it back right away since the difference in agro is so slight. i then keep on testing till i can nuke again or the mob runs and my skin is still up after the fight. keep in mind this is not every situation and is only the way to go if you have to do your max damamge without dying (also keep in mind that rooting is not an option with these guys since they all con red and any root that manages to catch is broken way too quikly).  thats about it, just wanted to throw out that tactic for a different situation.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
